      <hedline>
        <hl1>CHILE TO BE INVITED INTO TRADE BLOC</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>South American common market, or Mercosur, is expected to invite Chile to join trade bloc in early September; negotiations will try to bridge gap between Chile's 9 percent import duty, and Mercosur's tariffs, which start at 15 percent (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The South American common market, or Mercosur, is expected to invite Chile to join the trade bloc in early September. Negotiations will try to bridge the gap between Chile's 9 percent import duty, and Mercosur's tariffs, which start at 15 percent. Mercosur is composed of Brazil, Argentina, Uruguay and Paraguay.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich (NYT)</p>
      </block>
